reviews.text:
I was exploring Reddit for the best pizza in Utah, and Victor's Pizza Co continually topped people's list, so I had to give it a try. We ordered a 14" Royale with Cheese, a 16" half Chopper and half Mia, a 12" Taj Mahal, 6 pcs Mango Habanero Chicken Wings, 6pcs Spicy Buffalo Chicken Wings, and a "You Never Can Tell" Raspberry Pie. For the record, the raspberry dessert pie was an over-the-moon highlight for us. The whole family fought over every slice, so I highly recommend. All the pizzas were excellent. The general consensus was individuals tended to favor the pie they had requested, and only liked the pies they hadn't. So trust your eyes and your gut when ordering and you'll land a home run. For me, the Chopper was #1, and I plan on ordering The Gimp, Honey Bunny, Marvin, and Bad Mother Clucker on future visits. The wings are good and meaty, but the Spicy Buffalo had no spice. Still good, but zero heat. I enjoyed the heat and flavor from the Mango Habanero though. Did I mention the raspberry pie? Seriously, you've got to add it to your order. I'm still having food dreams about it.

The staff here are phenomenal. If I was a recruiter seeking customer service staff, I'd pull directly from the employees at Victor's. I called my order in, and the gal on the phone was friendly, helpful, and went out of her way to get me a good deal. I really appreciated her going above and beyond. Picking up the pizza in store was equally as good of an experience.

The atmosphere of the restaurant is awesome. I love the decor, and wish I could've eaten in house (although the A/C was out so maybe it was better I couldn't this time round). The only negative is parking. I'm still not sure where you're supposed to park, but I snagged a spot at the restaurant next door for a quick pickup.

Victor's Pizza Co is an awesome pizza spot and I love the local business. It's a pricier place for pizza, especially compared to the big chains, but it's quality and filling so you get your bang for your buck. Now that I've found Victor's, I'll continue to darken their doors and keep their ovens firing.

I have wanted to try Victor's for a long time and I'm so glad I finally did! It is phenomenal pizza and some of the best cheese bread I've ever had, it has more garlic than most places and it's fantastic. A lot of the toppings were hiding under the cheese, so the there's more than meets the eye initially, yum!

The style of pizza reminds me of a small hometown mom and pop kind of pizza place and it is delicious!

We were hungry for cheese pizza. There are 2 or 3 other pizza places closer to me but I wanted something different. I ordered online, drove over and called in for curbside pickup. The guy in charge was short staffed, basically cooking, running food and maybe the register. I was injured and he brought my pizza curbside with utensils, napkins and plates. That was so nice. I drove home; my friend and I sat down for a slice. The cheese pizza was perfect. It was extra toasted, just the way we like it. The cheese was bubbly, gooey, and crispy in the best parts. Oh my gosh! The red SAUCE is fabulous! It has the right amount of spice in it. Sweet, tangy, and cooked just right. A plain cheese pizza is the best way to try the sauce because it's the sauce that makes it taste so good!!

Service was very friendly, helpful, good. Pizza (large with three toppings), was sadly just ok‚Ä¶ have had better, had worse. Was really looking hoping for a pizza that would be ‚Äúwow‚Äù. While sitting there see a lot of door dash and such customers, so they do a great amount of business, which is awesome! Will have to try again sometime.

Pretty cozy lil place with above average pizza, wings and bread sticks.  The
atmosphere's pretty neat, the staffs super friendly and they have a pretty big selection of things to order.  My only change would be the pizza crust. It would have been better it it was cooked a lil bit more and not so soft.  Otherwise amazing.   I'll be back.

detailedReviews.text: Victor's Pizza is my go-to pizza place in Salt Lake City! I judge a pizza by how the pepperonis are cooked! Cupped with slightly burned edges, you got it right. My usual is the Italian sausage and pepperoni. I can't say I've tried the multiple specialty pizzas. I can only assume they're just as good as the usual. They're a family friendly, good customer service, local business. Support local is what we do now. And they deserve all the support! Thank you for filling my delivery pizza needs üôÇ I mean there's lots of good pizza places in Salt Lake, and you're one that should be known.

detailedReviews.author: Orion Patch
detailedReviews.text: Incredibly good pizza.  Chef Victor's complex sauces and fluffy but crispy dough makes for one of the best local pizzas around!

detailedReviews.author: Cindy Layton
detailedReviews.text: This is a little place.. however there are places to sit AND the pizza is delicious.  Service was fantastic!!!   We will be going again üëç

detailedReviews.author: Sage Anderson
detailedReviews.text: Best pizza i've had in SLC area. As a fellow tarantino film lover, im obsessed with the pulp fiction theme. I got "the Gimp" and it was delicious. I also got to try the house spicy ranch which was TO DIE FOR. you will not be disappointed!

strengthsPerceived: Customers consistently praise the exceptional customer service, highlighting instances where the manager personally delivered a replacement pizza and provided free drinks. - review management can highlight this positive aspect

positive.author: Donald
positive.text: I ordered thru dorr dash and the dasher carried my pizza like a book in a grocery bag so my pizza looked like a car wreck in a box I was seriously pissy but knew it wasn't victors pizzas fault I couldn't find the complaint place on dash site and the dasher ran from me to his car so I called victors and explained the problem just to let them know so they can tell door dash about their employee....... And next thing you know I'm getting a call from the manager cuz he was 5 min from my house with a new pizza and he added a drink. That's how business is done the pizza is the best in the valley if not the country and I've been around. I will never get pizza anywhere else I don't know the managers name but believe I won't ever forget the dashers name

neutral.author: Valerie Berger
neutral.text: Definitely worth ordering from but get it to go. I ordered pizza and a cheese stick. The crust was light airy with a little crispy perfection. The pizza was loaded with cheese and toppings so every bite had something on it. I originally wanted to dine in but the atmosphere was suffocating. It was humid and hot. I have great sympathy for the employees. Next to those ovens, it must be exhausting. Some somple fans would solve the problem. Its not a big space. Would definitely order another pizza from there.

negative.author: Magic HAT
negative.text: I'm reviewing this pizza differently because I'm from the East Coast from the pizza capital in Connecticut and I must say that this has to be the worst pizza I have ever tasted and I'll basically eat any pizza but it was just hard getting through two slices of this garbage this pizza was undercooked, very doughy, the crust was really not that crispy this thing was so floppy it was sad The sauce tasted like something out of a can so I can say I can basically give you a 1.3 out of 10 for your pizza.. again this review is just my own and I encourage everybody to try this place.

negative.author: Marii Sof
negative.text: The food was very bad. This is the second chance I've given them to try their pizza and I'm very disappointed. The bread is very hard, the cheese is also very hard, and they let me burn the pepperoni, as well as the bread. It seems like they're reheated pizzas, not freshly made.
